narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would not because ALEKS on top of problem sets was too much.

Chemistry 012 is an introductory chemistry course which is taught very vaguely, yet has a very large work load. I would not recommend that a fellow student take this class; I find that my high school Honors Chemistry class was much better than this course. I would recommend that future students take Chemistry 114 instead of this course as the content is very similar, yet it seems to be better explained in 114.
It is a waste of time.
I would recommend Chem 012 to another student. I found it to be a very rewarding class.

I would say that Chemistry 012 01, an additional section for chemistry, is helpful, but not something that every student NEEDS to attend. I would recommend it to students who need the extra help to succeed in the class.
Be prepared for a class full of online assignments in addition to Problem Sets.
I personally would not, but I can see why people may want to take the course.
I would recommended this class to a fellow student as a very good way of gaining a general background to chemistry from little or no previous experience in this field.
This was just a regular and sometimes helpful chem section. Nothing special.
Yes, I thought it was a good class. I would definitely recommend taking good notes while reading the chapters and understanding the lessons in class.
Helpful but not essential to your success in the class
